cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.NE, cs.CV 

This paper is about improving the performance of semantic role labeling (SRL) using a novel model called associated memory network (AMN). SRL is a task in natural language processing (NLP), which falls under the category of computational linguistics (cs.CL). The proposed model uses attention mechanisms, which are commonly used in machine learning and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also mentions comparing different strategies for selecting associated sentences and merging labels, which involves optimization and experimentation, falling under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and neural networks (cs.NE). Finally, the paper uses CoNLL-2009 benchmark datasets, which are commonly used in computer vision (cs.CV) and NLP research.
